<br>
&quot;All right, let me see if I understand the logic of this correctly. We are going to ignore the United Nations in order to make clear to Saddam Hussein that the United Nations cannot be ignored. &quot;<br>
<br>
No, we're going to war to disarm Iraq because it presents a threat to us.  This is not against any UN resolutions.  The UN has said nothing about military action in Iraq as they cannot agree on any resolutions.  Thus, the UN has no opinion at all in any unified sense.<br>
<br>
&quot;We're going to wage war to preserve the UN's ability to avert war. The paramount principle is that the UN's word must be taken seriously, and if we have to subvert its word to guarantee that it is, then by gum, we will.&quot;<br>
<br>
No we are going to war to disarm Saddam so he doesn't use his WMD against the US.  We aren't subverting the word of the UN as the UN has been unable to pass any resolutions on the matter of military force against Iraq.<br>
<br>
&quot;Peace is too important not to take up arms to defend. Am I getting this right?&quot;<br>
<br>
No, freedom is too important not to take up arms to defend.  Not peace.<br>
<br>
&quot;Further, if the only way to bring democracy to Iraq is to vitiate the democracy of the Security Council, then we are honor-bound to do that too, because democracy, as we define it, is too important to be stopped by a little thing like democracy as they define it.<br>
<br>
We aren't going against the UN here.  The UN has not in any way condemned military action against Iraq.  It has simply failed to support it.  Thus, the UN has no opinion on the matter at all whatsoever.  For the UN to have an opinioin, a resolution would have to be passed, and that has not happened regarding US led military action.<br>
<br>
&quot;Also, in dealing with a man who brooks no dissension at home, we cannot afford dissension among ourselves. We must speak with one voice against Saddam Hussein's failure to allow opposing voices to be heard.&quot;<br>
<br>
Bush has publicly said that people have a right to protest and he respects that.  We have made no attempts to suppress free speech.  However, freedom of speech does not mean freedom to dictate policy.  Even if it did, in the last poll I saw 71 percent of Americans supported president Bush's policies, 20 percent opposed, the rest were undecided.<br>
<br>
&quot;We are sending our gathered might to the Persian Gulf to make the point that might does not make right, as Saddam Hussein seems to think it does.&quot;<br>
<br>
No, we are not basing our right to act in Iraq on our might.   We are just lucky that we have the might to enforce what we believe, for other reasons, is right.  Then again, perhaps it's not luck.  Perhaps pursuit of democratic ideals has led this country to the prosperity that has made it a military/economic superpower.<br>
<br>
&quot;And we are twisting the arms of the opposition until it agrees to let us oust a regime that twists the arms of the opposition.&quot;<br>
<br>
We aren't twisting their arms at all.  They are doing what they want, we are doing what we want.  We have no power to force them to do anything.  This is in contrast to Saddam who will have your tongue surgically removed for disagreeing with him.<br>
<br>
&quot;We cannot leave in power a dictator who ignores his own people.And if our people, and people elsewhere in the world, fail to understand that, then we have no choice but to ignore them.&quot;<br>
<br>
Once again, I quote the poll that says that 71 percent of Americans support President Bush, 20 percent oppose, the rest are undecided.  That doesn't sound like Bush is ignoring public policy.  Sounds to me like not ousting Saddam would be ignoring our people. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter>Vazaelle.com Community Center</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30>The Real World</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://www.vazaelle.com">Vazaelle.com</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.245d<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

